1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:01,600
 - Thank you, Francesca.

2
00:00:01,600 --> 00:00:02,960
 Oh, a lot of pressure.

3
00:00:02,960 --> 00:00:04,640
 But thank you so much for coming in.

4
00:00:04,640 --> 00:00:06,040
 Thank you so much for, you know,

5
00:00:06,040 --> 00:00:07,400
 worshiping together the Lord.

6
00:00:07,400 --> 00:00:09,580
 I think this is such a powerful moment for us

7
00:00:09,580 --> 00:00:13,040
 just to come and be in the presence of God, yeah?

8
00:00:13,040 --> 00:00:17,080
 Well, seven years ago, I handed in my resignation letter.

9
00:00:17,080 --> 00:00:19,800
 I quit the job that I was doing for nine years

10
00:00:19,800 --> 00:00:23,560
 in a primary school, and I went to Australia.

11
00:00:23,560 --> 00:00:25,520
 Well, you live in Hong, we all live in Hong Kong,

12
00:00:25,520 --> 00:00:28,920
 and we know how packed our timetable is.

13
00:00:28,920 --> 00:00:31,120
 And I'm not just talking about the timetable

14
00:00:31,120 --> 00:00:34,120
 for getting up, going to work, coming back,

15
00:00:34,120 --> 00:00:35,680
 we have to make dinner, we have to go to bed,

16
00:00:35,680 --> 00:00:37,440
 and we have to start everything again.

17
00:00:37,440 --> 00:00:39,200
 It's not about that timetable.

18
00:00:39,200 --> 00:00:43,200
 It's more about like, when do you start school?

19
00:00:43,200 --> 00:00:45,280
 Do I start at two year old or three year old?

20
00:00:45,280 --> 00:00:47,280
 You know, do I finish school,

21
00:00:47,280 --> 00:00:49,900
 do I have a time for my gap year or not?

22
00:00:49,900 --> 00:00:51,200
 When do I get married?

23
00:00:51,200 --> 00:00:53,560
 There's a timetable to get married, to get pregnant,

24
00:00:53,560 --> 00:00:55,680
 and then to buy a house.

25
00:00:55,680 --> 00:00:59,320
 All these are so jam-packed that there's little

26
00:00:59,320 --> 00:01:00,960
 for us to move about.

27
00:01:00,960 --> 00:01:04,320
 It feels like everything is set on a timetable,

28
00:01:04,320 --> 00:01:07,480
 every moment scheduled, and every detail planned

29
00:01:07,480 --> 00:01:09,440
 with little room for mistakes.

30
00:01:09,440 --> 00:01:11,640
 So when I moved to Australia,

31
00:01:11,640 --> 00:01:15,200
 it felt like stepping into a completely new world,

32
00:01:15,200 --> 00:01:16,720
 one without a map.

33
00:01:16,720 --> 00:01:19,640
 No one's telling me what is going to happen next,

34
00:01:19,640 --> 00:01:23,000
 no plan in my hand, with just a wide space

35
00:01:23,000 --> 00:01:25,520
 full of possibilities.

36
00:01:25,520 --> 00:01:28,320
 Well, for me, the change is not just about work.

37
00:01:28,320 --> 00:01:32,640
 It's about giving myself a chance to rediscover who I am

38
00:01:32,640 --> 00:01:36,840
 and to step out of all the boxes that people have put me in

39
00:01:36,840 --> 00:01:40,720
 and to explore new things and to find a new me.

40
00:01:40,720 --> 00:01:42,840
 Well, the first new me that I discovered,

41
00:01:42,840 --> 00:01:44,920
 that is that I have natural curly hair.

42
00:01:44,920 --> 00:01:47,920
 So when I moved to Australia,

43
00:01:47,920 --> 00:01:50,560
 I stopped straightening my hair and found out that,

44
00:01:50,560 --> 00:01:53,280
 wow, actually, this is, I have curly hair

45
00:01:53,280 --> 00:01:56,160
 and I look pretty good in it, right?

46
00:01:56,160 --> 00:01:58,000
 Okay, there's a little delay, but I accept that.

47
00:01:58,000 --> 00:02:00,200
 It's okay. (laughs)

48
00:02:00,200 --> 00:02:02,640
 Well, and it's not just about the outer,

49
00:02:02,640 --> 00:02:08,800
 the facial appearance that was not a newer,

50
00:02:08,800 --> 00:02:11,400
 but in the places, in that place,

51
00:02:11,400 --> 00:02:14,640
 I discovered that my faith was often small,

52
00:02:14,640 --> 00:02:16,440
 that there were many uncertainties

53
00:02:16,440 --> 00:02:19,360
 and insecurities in myself.

54
00:02:19,400 --> 00:02:21,480
 And in those moments, I began to learn

55
00:02:21,480 --> 00:02:25,600
 how to rebuild my faith and how to grab hold of Jesus

56
00:02:25,600 --> 00:02:27,960
 when I feel that I'm sinking.

57
00:02:27,960 --> 00:02:31,040
 I was truly living in the no-map season,

58
00:02:31,040 --> 00:02:35,000
 but it wasn't by accident that I stumbled upon Australia.

59
00:02:35,000 --> 00:02:37,240
 It wasn't that I got lost, I got on a plane,

60
00:02:37,240 --> 00:02:39,360
 and I happened to be in Australia.

61
00:02:39,360 --> 00:02:44,360
 No, I made a conscious decision to enter into that space.

62
00:02:44,360 --> 00:02:48,840
 I want to find myself again, to try new paths,

63
00:02:48,840 --> 00:02:52,920
 to give myself space, to quietly hear God's voice,

64
00:02:52,920 --> 00:02:56,280
 and to grow in a community that loved Him.

65
00:02:56,280 --> 00:02:58,440
 The vision for our church this year

66
00:02:58,440 --> 00:03:02,400
 is about being in the uncharted,

67
00:03:02,400 --> 00:03:05,840
 but let me be clear, we're not just drifting along,

68
00:03:05,840 --> 00:03:08,320
 waiting to see what's going to happen,

69
00:03:08,320 --> 00:03:10,880
 following trends, or copying some 10-step

70
00:03:10,880 --> 00:03:13,160
 to grow our church formula.

71
00:03:13,160 --> 00:03:16,920
 Instead, we're intentionally placing ourselves

72
00:03:16,920 --> 00:03:20,320
 in a position where God has room to lead us,

73
00:03:20,320 --> 00:03:24,520
 to show us new direction and new possibilities.

74
00:03:24,520 --> 00:03:28,240
 We want to trust the Holy Spirit to be our compass

75
00:03:28,240 --> 00:03:31,200
 and not rely on the world's map.

76
00:03:31,200 --> 00:03:34,760
 We want to be a people who are willing to step out,

77
00:03:34,760 --> 00:03:37,240
 to take risks, and to obey God,

78
00:03:37,240 --> 00:03:39,760
 not because we already have the answers

79
00:03:39,760 --> 00:03:42,840
 or the roadmap to it, but because we know

80
00:03:42,840 --> 00:03:45,200
 that it is God who truly does.

81
00:03:46,320 --> 00:03:50,960
 Honestly, living in unknown and the uncharted

82
00:03:50,960 --> 00:03:53,240
 is uncomfortable.

83
00:03:53,240 --> 00:03:56,120
 Sometimes we think if we are walking with God

84
00:03:56,120 --> 00:03:59,240
 and the Holy Spirit, things will be smooth,

85
00:03:59,240 --> 00:04:02,320
 but actually, it can be even harder.

86
00:04:02,320 --> 00:04:05,840
 With more challenges, God often leads us

87
00:04:05,840 --> 00:04:08,200
 into places that we've never been

88
00:04:08,200 --> 00:04:10,600
 or things we have never done before.

89
00:04:10,600 --> 00:04:12,160
 There are no guarantees.

90
00:04:12,160 --> 00:04:15,240
 And maybe you feel like that right now.

91
00:04:16,120 --> 00:04:18,840
 Maybe you're walking on a road

92
00:04:18,840 --> 00:04:21,520
 where you can't see what's happening next.

93
00:04:21,520 --> 00:04:25,400
 Maybe God is asking you to let go of something

94
00:04:25,400 --> 00:04:27,840
 that feels safest to you.

95
00:04:27,840 --> 00:04:31,400
 Maybe let go of a relationship, a job,

96
00:04:31,400 --> 00:04:33,360
 a role, or identity.

97
00:04:33,360 --> 00:04:37,480
 Or maybe in this season, you are just tired,

98
00:04:37,480 --> 00:04:41,840
 too tired to hope, too tired to hear God's voice

99
00:04:41,840 --> 00:04:43,040
 above the noise.

100
00:04:44,040 --> 00:04:48,320
 The irony is the more seriously you try to respond to God,

101
00:04:48,320 --> 00:04:51,520
 to listen for His voice and let Him guide you,

102
00:04:51,520 --> 00:04:55,240
 the more difficulties, doubts, and risks seems to appear,

103
00:04:55,240 --> 00:04:58,000
 and the narrower the road feels.

104
00:04:58,000 --> 00:05:01,240
 Sometimes you even ask, "God, I'm already trying.

105
00:05:01,240 --> 00:05:03,360
 "I'm already responding to you.

106
00:05:03,360 --> 00:05:06,080
 "Why is this still so hard?

107
00:05:06,080 --> 00:05:09,200
 "Why am I so unsure?"

108
00:05:09,200 --> 00:05:12,760
 And this is the tension that we are living in right now,

109
00:05:12,760 --> 00:05:15,320
 this tension in the unknown.

110
00:05:15,320 --> 00:05:17,440
 You have the Holy Spirit with you,

111
00:05:17,440 --> 00:05:20,560
 but you also still face your own fears,

112
00:05:20,560 --> 00:05:23,800
 your doubts, your insecurities, and your habits.

113
00:05:23,800 --> 00:05:27,200
 Today, we're going to look at chapter four

114
00:05:27,200 --> 00:05:30,440
 to see how in a season of unknowns,

115
00:05:30,440 --> 00:05:33,280
 Peter and John modeled what it means

116
00:05:33,280 --> 00:05:37,840
 to take a step forward even when the path isn't clear,

117
00:05:37,840 --> 00:05:41,120
 and how we, too, can find courage and faith

118
00:05:41,120 --> 00:05:45,080
 to keep going through uncertainty, insecurities,

119
00:05:45,080 --> 00:05:46,280
 and even fear.

120
00:05:46,280 --> 00:05:49,440
 Let us have a look at the first,

121
00:05:49,440 --> 00:05:53,240
 first one to seven in Acts chapter four.

122
00:05:53,240 --> 00:05:58,400
 This is to give all of you a little background.

123
00:05:58,400 --> 00:06:01,000
 Peter and John just performed a miracle,

124
00:06:01,000 --> 00:06:04,960
 and he helped the lame man who was lame for 40 years

125
00:06:04,960 --> 00:06:07,560
 to rise up and walk, and everyone cheered,

126
00:06:07,560 --> 00:06:09,960
 and he gave a sermon, a priesthood sermon

127
00:06:09,960 --> 00:06:12,920
 to all the Jews around the area.

128
00:06:12,920 --> 00:06:16,440
 But, here it goes, the priest and the captain

129
00:06:16,440 --> 00:06:20,400
 of the temple guard and the seduces came up to Peter

130
00:06:20,400 --> 00:06:23,840
 and John while they were speaking to the people.

131
00:06:23,840 --> 00:06:26,440
 They were greatly disturbed because the apostles

132
00:06:26,440 --> 00:06:29,280
 were teaching the people, proclaiming Jesus,

133
00:06:29,280 --> 00:06:31,080
 the resurrection of the dead.

134
00:06:31,080 --> 00:06:34,880
 They seized Peter and John, and because it was evening,

135
00:06:34,880 --> 00:06:37,600
 they put him in jail until the next day.

136
00:06:37,600 --> 00:06:39,760
 But many who heard the message believed,

137
00:06:39,760 --> 00:06:44,440
 so the number of men who believed grew to about 5,000.

138
00:06:44,440 --> 00:06:47,040
 The next day, the rulers, the elders,

139
00:06:47,040 --> 00:06:50,280
 and the teachers of the Lord met in Jerusalem.

140
00:06:50,280 --> 00:06:54,160
 Annas, the high priest, was there, and so were Caiaphas,

141
00:06:54,160 --> 00:06:58,000
 John, Alexander, and other of the high priest family.

142
00:06:58,000 --> 00:07:00,480
 They had Peter and John brought before them

143
00:07:00,480 --> 00:07:02,800
 and began to question them.

144
00:07:02,800 --> 00:07:07,400
 By what power or what name do you do this?

145
00:07:07,400 --> 00:07:09,360
 At that time, present at the council

146
00:07:09,360 --> 00:07:11,480
 were Annas, the high priest, Caiaphas,

147
00:07:11,480 --> 00:07:13,920
 and other high priestly family members

148
00:07:13,920 --> 00:07:15,960
 like John and Alexander.

149
00:07:15,960 --> 00:07:20,040
 These were the high-ranking, most powerful religious leaders

150
00:07:20,040 --> 00:07:21,800
 in Jewish society.

151
00:07:21,800 --> 00:07:26,400
 The high priest family not only held enormous authority,

152
00:07:26,400 --> 00:07:30,080
 but also in religious matters, in politics,

153
00:07:30,080 --> 00:07:33,000
 wealth, and people's lives.

154
00:07:33,000 --> 00:07:35,760
 They questioned them, using the authority

155
00:07:35,760 --> 00:07:38,840
 to remind everyone who is in charge.

156
00:07:38,840 --> 00:07:44,400
 By what power or what name did you do this?

157
00:07:44,400 --> 00:07:47,120
 Sometimes, these kind of questions

158
00:07:47,120 --> 00:07:50,240
 are what others say to us, and sometimes

159
00:07:50,240 --> 00:07:53,440
 is what we say to ourselves.

160
00:07:53,440 --> 00:07:56,000
 It might not sound exactly the same,

161
00:07:56,000 --> 00:07:59,600
 but if you look closely, the pattern is familiar.

162
00:07:59,600 --> 00:08:03,600
 The enemy is so good at using doubts, accusations,

163
00:08:03,600 --> 00:08:07,640
 and intimidation to make us question ourselves and stop us

164
00:08:07,640 --> 00:08:10,080
 from stepping forward.

165
00:08:10,080 --> 00:08:13,760
 In our daily lives, these voices could sound like,

166
00:08:13,760 --> 00:08:16,600
 who do you think you are?

167
00:08:16,600 --> 00:08:20,360
 When you want to step out in faith, to share your story,

168
00:08:20,360 --> 00:08:23,040
 you hear, who do you think you are?

169
00:08:23,040 --> 00:08:25,720
 You're not good enough, not holy enough.

170
00:08:25,720 --> 00:08:27,400
 You've messed up too many times.

171
00:08:27,400 --> 00:08:30,480
 Don't get involved.

172
00:08:30,480 --> 00:08:34,720
 What right do you have to live like this?

173
00:08:34,720 --> 00:08:38,080
 When you try to set boundaries, forgive or change,

174
00:08:38,080 --> 00:08:41,560
 there's that voice who says, you can do this.

175
00:08:41,560 --> 00:08:42,840
 What makes you so special?

176
00:08:42,840 --> 00:08:49,120
 Who gave you that right to believe God could use you?

177
00:08:49,120 --> 00:08:52,040
 When you start to dream and pray boldly,

178
00:08:52,040 --> 00:08:54,840
 you think, God wouldn't use someone like you.

179
00:08:54,840 --> 00:08:58,160
 Don't kid yourself.

180
00:08:58,160 --> 00:09:00,680
 Are you really forgiven?

181
00:09:00,680 --> 00:09:04,320
 Are you truly lovable?

182
00:09:04,320 --> 00:09:07,440
 When you try to walk in freedom and grace,

183
00:09:07,440 --> 00:09:10,920
 you find your past failures playing on repeat,

184
00:09:10,920 --> 00:09:16,320
 making you doubt whether God's grace is really enough for you.

185
00:09:16,320 --> 00:09:17,840
 Have you noticed?

186
00:09:17,840 --> 00:09:21,720
 These voices that always question, accuse, and make

187
00:09:21,720 --> 00:09:25,040
 us shrink back, go silent, and stop moving forward

188
00:09:25,040 --> 00:09:28,040
 in fear or shame sometimes.

189
00:09:28,040 --> 00:09:31,520
 The Bible calls Satan the accuser of our brothers.

190
00:09:31,520 --> 00:09:35,200
 His main goal is to make us forget who you are

191
00:09:35,200 --> 00:09:37,640
 and whose you are.

192
00:09:37,640 --> 00:09:41,520
 But look at how Peter and John answer these accusations.

193
00:09:41,520 --> 00:09:45,160
 In verse 8 to 14, it says, "Then Peter,

194
00:09:45,160 --> 00:09:47,960
 filled with the Holy Spirit, said to them,

195
00:09:47,960 --> 00:09:50,120
 'Rulers and elders of the people,

196
00:09:50,120 --> 00:09:52,600
 if we are being called to account today

197
00:09:52,600 --> 00:09:56,080
 for an act of kindness shown to a man who was lame

198
00:09:56,080 --> 00:09:58,840
 and are now being asked how he was healed,

199
00:09:58,840 --> 00:10:02,440
 then know this, you and all the people of Israel.

200
00:10:02,440 --> 00:10:05,680
 It is by the name of Jesus Christ of Nazareth,

201
00:10:05,680 --> 00:10:09,600
 whom you crucified, but whom God raised from the dead,

202
00:10:09,600 --> 00:10:12,400
 that this man stands before you healed.

203
00:10:12,400 --> 00:10:15,080
 Jesus is the stone you builders rejected,

204
00:10:15,080 --> 00:10:17,640
 which has become the cornerstone.

205
00:10:17,640 --> 00:10:20,480
 Salvation is found in no one else,

206
00:10:20,480 --> 00:10:24,000
 for there is no other name under heaven given to mankind

207
00:10:24,000 --> 00:10:27,360
 by which we must be saved.'

208
00:10:27,360 --> 00:10:29,960
 When they saw the courage of John and Peter

209
00:10:29,960 --> 00:10:33,360
 and realized that they were unschooled, ordinary men,

210
00:10:33,360 --> 00:10:34,840
 they were astonished.

211
00:10:34,840 --> 00:10:39,840
 And they took note that these men had been with Jesus.

212
00:10:39,840 --> 00:10:42,680
 But since they could see the man

213
00:10:42,680 --> 00:10:45,840
 who had been healed standing there with them,

214
00:10:45,840 --> 00:10:47,480
 there was nothing they could say.

215
00:10:47,480 --> 00:10:51,240
 There was nothing they could say.

216
00:10:51,240 --> 00:10:54,440
 The religious leader saw Peter and John's boldness

217
00:10:54,440 --> 00:10:55,800
 and were shocked.

218
00:10:55,800 --> 00:10:59,240
 They realized that these two are ordinary men,

219
00:10:59,240 --> 00:11:00,600
 not that they are stupid,

220
00:11:00,600 --> 00:11:03,280
 but they hadn't been trained in rabbinical schools

221
00:11:03,280 --> 00:11:04,880
 or Greek academies,

222
00:11:04,880 --> 00:11:08,280
 and hadn't learned how to debate in public.

223
00:11:08,280 --> 00:11:12,080
 Normally, someone like Peter, facing a council,

224
00:11:12,080 --> 00:11:14,640
 would have been terrified and speechless.

225
00:11:14,640 --> 00:11:17,400
 But Peter wasn't afraid at all.

226
00:11:17,400 --> 00:11:20,240
 He boldly pointed out that these leaders

227
00:11:20,240 --> 00:11:23,960
 had crucified the very one God sent, Jesus.

228
00:11:24,960 --> 00:11:27,080
 Peter and John were direct.

229
00:11:27,080 --> 00:11:28,800
 They didn't defend themselves,

230
00:11:28,800 --> 00:11:31,200
 trying to say, "No, I have the right to speak like this way.

231
00:11:31,200 --> 00:11:33,040
 "I can preach to people like that way."

232
00:11:33,040 --> 00:11:34,880
 They did not defend themselves.

233
00:11:34,880 --> 00:11:37,920
 He just very directly and very boldly

234
00:11:37,920 --> 00:11:40,520
 to point out who Jesus was.

235
00:11:40,520 --> 00:11:44,320
 He also revealed the leaders' real problem.

236
00:11:44,320 --> 00:11:48,560
 They valued their interest about God,

237
00:11:48,560 --> 00:11:49,920
 were self-righteous,

238
00:11:49,920 --> 00:11:53,760
 and refused to admit their own need of saving.

239
00:11:53,760 --> 00:11:56,480
 As a result, they missed the miracle

240
00:11:56,480 --> 00:11:59,000
 that Jesus did right in front of them

241
00:11:59,000 --> 00:12:00,440
 and missed God's grace.

242
00:12:00,440 --> 00:12:07,480
 His honesty came because he was truly walked with Jesus

243
00:12:07,480 --> 00:12:12,760
 and had been transformed by Him.

244
00:12:12,760 --> 00:12:16,240
 This courage is something no human training can give.

245
00:12:16,240 --> 00:12:20,480
 It is obvious to everyone that they had been with Jesus.

246
00:12:21,360 --> 00:12:23,720
 And what does it mean to be with Jesus?

247
00:12:23,720 --> 00:12:28,520
 When someone had truly been with Jesus, it shows.

248
00:12:28,520 --> 00:12:31,240
 Maybe you can already recognize these people

249
00:12:31,240 --> 00:12:33,480
 in church or in life,

250
00:12:33,480 --> 00:12:36,200
 that there's something different about them.

251
00:12:36,200 --> 00:12:39,320
 That peace is different.

252
00:12:39,320 --> 00:12:42,160
 The way that they understand you is different.

253
00:12:42,160 --> 00:12:45,480
 The kindness and empathy stands out.

254
00:12:45,480 --> 00:12:48,760
 They don't need to be the smartest or the most talented,

255
00:12:48,760 --> 00:12:51,720
 but you can sense something different in them,

256
00:12:51,720 --> 00:12:56,720
 a quality that is set apart, that is different.

257
00:12:56,720 --> 00:12:58,760
 And that is what holiness means.

258
00:12:58,760 --> 00:13:01,560
 It isn't just about moral perfection.

259
00:13:01,560 --> 00:13:05,800
 There's no sin at all, but also being set apart,

260
00:13:05,800 --> 00:13:08,720
 being shaped by what they do,

261
00:13:08,720 --> 00:13:11,360
 being shaped by God's presence.

262
00:13:11,360 --> 00:13:12,760
 When you love someone,

263
00:13:12,760 --> 00:13:15,480
 you wanna eat what they want to eat.

264
00:13:15,480 --> 00:13:17,600
 You try to learn their taste, right?

265
00:13:17,600 --> 00:13:20,000
 You try to understand what they're thinking.

266
00:13:20,000 --> 00:13:22,640
 You care about what they care about.

267
00:13:22,640 --> 00:13:26,320
 We are shaped by the ones we love.

268
00:13:26,320 --> 00:13:29,960
 When we truly love Jesus,

269
00:13:29,960 --> 00:13:33,160
 we let him shape our priorities,

270
00:13:33,160 --> 00:13:36,040
 our attitudes, and our responses.

271
00:13:36,040 --> 00:13:39,880
 It is about letting his heart change ours.

272
00:13:39,880 --> 00:13:44,880
 And that's how, in a world of accusations and competitions,

273
00:13:44,920 --> 00:13:47,720
 we can be a different kind of people.

274
00:13:47,720 --> 00:13:49,680
 We can be set apart.

275
00:13:49,680 --> 00:13:56,720
 And so they ordered them to withdraw from the Sanhedrin

276
00:13:56,720 --> 00:13:58,440
 and then confer together.

277
00:13:58,440 --> 00:14:02,240
 "What are we going to do with these men?" they ask.

278
00:14:02,240 --> 00:14:05,520
 Everyone living in Jerusalem knows

279
00:14:05,520 --> 00:14:09,920
 they have performed a notable sign, and we cannot deny it.

280
00:14:09,920 --> 00:14:11,920
 But to stop this thing from spreading

281
00:14:11,920 --> 00:14:13,800
 any further among the people,

282
00:14:13,800 --> 00:14:16,280
 we must warn them to speak no longer

283
00:14:16,280 --> 00:14:19,040
 to anyone in this name.

284
00:14:19,040 --> 00:14:22,360
 Even though the authorities saw

285
00:14:22,360 --> 00:14:24,920
 how undeniable the evidence is,

286
00:14:24,920 --> 00:14:27,480
 a healed man standing before them,

287
00:14:27,480 --> 00:14:29,880
 they refused to admit it.

288
00:14:29,880 --> 00:14:33,160
 Even if they denied the number of men

289
00:14:33,160 --> 00:14:36,920
 who believed had already reached 5,000.

290
00:14:36,920 --> 00:14:39,920
 This movement, this power is spreading fast,

291
00:14:40,160 --> 00:14:43,400
 and the leaders felt out of control.

292
00:14:43,400 --> 00:14:44,600
 And what could they do?

293
00:14:44,600 --> 00:14:49,240
 These religious leaders could arrest the apostles

294
00:14:49,240 --> 00:14:51,720
 and use their power to threaten them,

295
00:14:51,720 --> 00:14:54,440
 but they could not stop the gospel.

296
00:14:54,440 --> 00:14:55,960
 They could imprison people,

297
00:14:55,960 --> 00:14:58,400
 but they could not imprison God's work.

298
00:14:58,400 --> 00:15:00,680
 All the human tactics were powerless

299
00:15:00,680 --> 00:15:02,680
 compared to God's power.

300
00:15:02,680 --> 00:15:04,760
 That's always the way it is.

301
00:15:04,760 --> 00:15:08,000
 Those who oppose God try to suppress the truth,

302
00:15:08,000 --> 00:15:09,880
 but it never works.

303
00:15:09,880 --> 00:15:11,440
 All the accusations,

304
00:15:11,440 --> 00:15:13,880
 all the things that we have been listening

305
00:15:13,880 --> 00:15:16,680
 from when we were young up to when we're adult right now,

306
00:15:16,680 --> 00:15:19,280
 that the things that told us that you are not enough,

307
00:15:19,280 --> 00:15:21,640
 that you are not lovable, all these things,

308
00:15:21,640 --> 00:15:23,200
 they are just tactics,

309
00:15:23,200 --> 00:15:25,760
 but they cannot stop the power of the gospel

310
00:15:25,760 --> 00:15:27,440
 working out in your life.

311
00:15:27,440 --> 00:15:30,520
 All the question that you have been questioning

312
00:15:30,520 --> 00:15:33,720
 about yourself, we have to release them back to God

313
00:15:33,720 --> 00:15:36,640
 and tell God that this is what I'm hearing.

314
00:15:36,640 --> 00:15:38,160
 Is this from you?

315
00:15:38,160 --> 00:15:40,000
 I'm trying to walk with you.

316
00:15:40,000 --> 00:15:42,440
 I wanna be shaped by what you care about.

317
00:15:42,440 --> 00:15:44,480
 I want to know your priorities.

318
00:15:44,480 --> 00:15:47,680
 And if these thoughts, these things are not from you,

319
00:15:47,680 --> 00:15:49,600
 are not aligning from you,

320
00:15:49,600 --> 00:15:53,400
 the power of the gospel is going to work in my life

321
00:15:53,400 --> 00:15:57,360
 so that I will no longer, no longer be bound by the sin,

322
00:15:57,360 --> 00:16:00,120
 no longer be bound by these accusations.

323
00:16:00,120 --> 00:16:04,800
 Peter and John weren't fearless because they were brave.

324
00:16:04,800 --> 00:16:06,400
 They had walked with Jesus.

325
00:16:06,400 --> 00:16:08,000
 They had seen his miracles.

326
00:16:08,000 --> 00:16:10,680
 They watched him calm storms with a few words

327
00:16:10,680 --> 00:16:12,960
 and witnessed him heal the sick.

328
00:16:12,960 --> 00:16:16,840
 And most of all, seen him defeat death.

329
00:16:16,840 --> 00:16:19,720
 Their courage doesn't come from their personality

330
00:16:19,720 --> 00:16:23,280
 or training, it came from a real,

331
00:16:23,280 --> 00:16:26,440
 living relationship with Jesus.

332
00:16:26,440 --> 00:16:29,640
 It was a result of years of friendship,

333
00:16:29,640 --> 00:16:34,640
 of seeing him work, of being forgiven and restored by him.

334
00:16:34,640 --> 00:16:36,680
 With those experiences,

335
00:16:36,680 --> 00:16:41,680
 they knew that every threat and intimidation was nothing

336
00:16:41,680 --> 00:16:44,560
 compared to the power of God.

337
00:16:44,560 --> 00:16:50,760
 Even knowing their lives were at risk and the price was high,

338
00:16:50,760 --> 00:16:53,480
 they could keep going because they knew

339
00:16:53,480 --> 00:16:56,880
 the resurrected Lord was truly in charge.

340
00:16:56,880 --> 00:16:59,840
 Even at the hardest, scariest moment,

341
00:16:59,840 --> 00:17:03,200
 they could move forward with confidence.

342
00:17:03,200 --> 00:17:06,800
 Even when they feel scared, there could be courage

343
00:17:06,800 --> 00:17:11,440
 because God's will will be done and no one could stop God.

344
00:17:11,440 --> 00:17:16,000
 And that's why we need to walk with Jesus.

345
00:17:16,000 --> 00:17:19,920
 Only by staying close with him, knowing him,

346
00:17:19,920 --> 00:17:24,160
 and making him our foundation can we have the strength

347
00:17:24,160 --> 00:17:26,680
 to keep going even when things are tough.

348
00:17:26,680 --> 00:17:30,560
 And speaking of courage in the face of fear,

349
00:17:30,560 --> 00:17:32,200
 I have my own story to tell.

350
00:17:33,080 --> 00:17:36,800
 Actually, this is not the first time for me to apply

351
00:17:36,800 --> 00:17:39,400
 for a full-time role at the Vine Church.

352
00:17:39,400 --> 00:17:42,400
 Remember I talked about how I left my teaching job,

353
00:17:42,400 --> 00:17:46,800
 went to Australia, I came back and I still continue to teach

354
00:17:46,800 --> 00:17:50,200
 but then there was a moment when there was an opening

355
00:17:50,200 --> 00:17:52,920
 in the Vine One Chi and I had a chance to interview

356
00:17:52,920 --> 00:17:55,720
 for a full-time position at the Vine.

357
00:17:55,720 --> 00:17:57,360
 The interview went very smooth.

358
00:17:57,360 --> 00:18:00,120
 It was during COVID and I have to do it in a separate room

359
00:18:00,120 --> 00:18:03,040
 but inside, like the interview went smooth,

360
00:18:03,040 --> 00:18:06,080
 but inside I was so nervous.

361
00:18:06,080 --> 00:18:09,720
 I was so, I had so much fear in my heart

362
00:18:09,720 --> 00:18:14,560
 because I already had a very stable job, a teaching job.

363
00:18:14,560 --> 00:18:16,920
 Life was comfortable.

364
00:18:16,920 --> 00:18:21,680
 It was hard to imagine making such a big change in my age.

365
00:18:21,680 --> 00:18:22,880
 I think I've told you guys before,

366
00:18:22,880 --> 00:18:27,000
 I handed my assignment in university using a floppy disk.

367
00:18:27,000 --> 00:18:30,280
 Those that laughed, you're in my age group.

368
00:18:30,280 --> 00:18:35,080
 It was hard to imagine having to make such a big change

369
00:18:35,080 --> 00:18:39,320
 at my age, stepping into something so different, even harder.

370
00:18:39,320 --> 00:18:42,120
 This decision meant giving up a lot

371
00:18:42,120 --> 00:18:44,440
 and facing pressure from my family.

372
00:18:44,440 --> 00:18:48,160
 They loved me and want me to have a stable, comfortable life

373
00:18:48,160 --> 00:18:52,240
 so it was hard for them to understand or support me.

374
00:18:52,240 --> 00:18:54,960
 So in the end, I didn't go through with the interview.

375
00:18:56,080 --> 00:18:59,440
 A few years later, I got involved with church planting,

376
00:18:59,440 --> 00:19:02,600
 serving wholeheartedly as a volunteer.

377
00:19:02,600 --> 00:19:05,160
 Looking back, I see God's grace.

378
00:19:05,160 --> 00:19:08,680
 He didn't blame me because June, you gave up last time.

379
00:19:08,680 --> 00:19:10,880
 Why do I still give you another chance?

380
00:19:10,880 --> 00:19:12,240
 No more chances for you.

381
00:19:12,240 --> 00:19:15,000
 He didn't blame me for feeling scared.

382
00:19:15,000 --> 00:19:17,760
 He didn't blame me for backing out

383
00:19:17,760 --> 00:19:21,800
 but he gave me time to grow, to learn to love him,

384
00:19:21,800 --> 00:19:24,160
 to love the church more deeply.

385
00:19:24,160 --> 00:19:27,880
 Serving this time felt different, deep inside.

386
00:19:27,880 --> 00:19:31,880
 The past years, I've kept experiencing his grace and love

387
00:19:31,880 --> 00:19:36,880
 and realized that I've always been accepted and led by him.

388
00:19:36,880 --> 00:19:41,920
 So this time, choosing again to go full-time in ministry,

389
00:19:41,920 --> 00:19:45,000
 the fear is still there and it is very real.

390
00:19:45,000 --> 00:19:49,160
 It still means that I have to let go of what I see

391
00:19:49,160 --> 00:19:52,120
 in my future and facing uncertainty.

392
00:19:52,120 --> 00:19:54,280
 And my family's worries,

393
00:19:54,280 --> 00:19:59,280
 but God's love is helping me slowly let go of my fears.

394
00:19:59,280 --> 00:20:02,720
 Even with all the unknowns and sacrifices,

395
00:20:02,720 --> 00:20:07,720
 I'm more certain than ever that what God gives me

396
00:20:07,720 --> 00:20:11,520
 will be enough and his strength

397
00:20:11,520 --> 00:20:15,400
 will lead me through every single step.

398
00:20:15,400 --> 00:20:19,560
 I still can't see past this year or the next year,

399
00:20:19,560 --> 00:20:22,600
 but I know that I can see past all these years

400
00:20:22,600 --> 00:20:25,400
 right to the end of my life that God is going to be there

401
00:20:25,400 --> 00:20:27,440
 and he is not going to forfeit me.

402
00:20:27,440 --> 00:20:29,320
 He's not going to let me go.

403
00:20:29,320 --> 00:20:31,560
 That this provision, this grace,

404
00:20:31,560 --> 00:20:33,560
 that this love that he has for me

405
00:20:33,560 --> 00:20:35,640
 to provide for me in this journey,

406
00:20:35,640 --> 00:20:39,080
 that he will provide in all the areas of my life.

407
00:20:39,080 --> 00:20:42,360
 That this grace that I'm having, that receiving,

408
00:20:42,360 --> 00:20:45,360
 is not going to be just enough for today,

409
00:20:45,360 --> 00:20:48,120
 but for the rest of my journey with him.

410
00:20:49,120 --> 00:20:54,120
 I've realized that courage isn't the absence of fear,

411
00:20:54,120 --> 00:20:57,720
 but fearing the right one.

412
00:20:57,720 --> 00:21:01,960
 There are many reasons why I could be fearful.

413
00:21:01,960 --> 00:21:06,200
 I could be fearful financially or about my pathway

414
00:21:06,200 --> 00:21:08,240
 or my family or what I'm going to do

415
00:21:08,240 --> 00:21:11,200
 when it's the end of the pathway.

416
00:21:11,200 --> 00:21:14,080
 There are so many things that I could be fearful of,

417
00:21:14,080 --> 00:21:17,600
 but that's another meaning to the word fear, is to honor.

418
00:21:18,560 --> 00:21:20,400
 I honor my God.

419
00:21:20,400 --> 00:21:22,840
 I honor Jesus in my life.

420
00:21:22,840 --> 00:21:25,960
 And that is going to give me the courage

421
00:21:25,960 --> 00:21:27,160
 to take the next step.

422
00:21:27,160 --> 00:21:30,960
 Now let's take a look at Peter and John,

423
00:21:30,960 --> 00:21:33,480
 how they responded when the authorities

424
00:21:33,480 --> 00:21:35,080
 tried to silence them.

425
00:21:35,080 --> 00:21:38,360
 Then they called them in again

426
00:21:38,360 --> 00:21:42,320
 and commanded them not to speak or teach at all

427
00:21:42,320 --> 00:21:43,800
 in the name of Jesus.

428
00:21:43,800 --> 00:21:46,440
 But Peter and John replied,

429
00:21:46,440 --> 00:21:48,840
 "Which is right in God's eyes,

430
00:21:48,840 --> 00:21:53,120
 "listen to you or to him, you be the judges.

431
00:21:53,120 --> 00:21:56,440
 "As for us, we cannot help speaking about

432
00:21:56,440 --> 00:21:59,360
 "what we have seen and heard."

433
00:21:59,360 --> 00:22:02,520
 When they were ordered to be quiet

434
00:22:02,520 --> 00:22:04,760
 and stop talking about Jesus,

435
00:22:04,760 --> 00:22:06,280
 Peter and John answered,

436
00:22:06,280 --> 00:22:11,280
 "You decide whether it is right for us to obey you or God.

437
00:22:11,280 --> 00:22:14,360
 "But as for us, we cannot help speaking about

438
00:22:14,360 --> 00:22:17,000
 "what we have seen and heard."

439
00:22:17,000 --> 00:22:21,680
 What have you seen and heard lately from Jesus?

440
00:22:21,680 --> 00:22:26,280
 That you go, "I've heard this,

441
00:22:26,280 --> 00:22:28,120
 "I cannot stop talking about it."

442
00:22:28,120 --> 00:22:30,200
 Just like you had some really delicious food.

443
00:22:30,200 --> 00:22:32,240
 You went to a restaurant, it go, "So delicious."

444
00:22:32,240 --> 00:22:34,240
 You can't help but tell everyone around you

445
00:22:34,240 --> 00:22:36,320
 to go and try that place.

446
00:22:36,320 --> 00:22:37,320
 It is like this.

447
00:22:37,320 --> 00:22:40,840
 Have you seen and taste the goodness of God?

448
00:22:40,840 --> 00:22:43,080
 It's not that he isn't there,

449
00:22:43,080 --> 00:22:46,000
 but we need to place ourself in a position

450
00:22:46,000 --> 00:22:49,080
 where we could hear him and taste his goodness

451
00:22:49,080 --> 00:22:53,680
 and be revealed his glorious love and grace to us.

452
00:22:53,680 --> 00:22:59,840
 There are a lot of layers to Peter and John's answer here.

453
00:22:59,840 --> 00:23:02,880
 First, they actually flipped the situation around.

454
00:23:02,880 --> 00:23:05,720
 What's remarkable is that through the wisdom

455
00:23:05,720 --> 00:23:09,040
 that comes from being filled by the Holy Spirit,

456
00:23:09,040 --> 00:23:11,680
 Peter and John were able to completely

457
00:23:11,680 --> 00:23:13,440
 turn the situation around.

458
00:23:13,440 --> 00:23:16,720
 Just moments before, they were the ones on trial,

459
00:23:16,720 --> 00:23:19,240
 being questioned, accused, and judged

460
00:23:19,240 --> 00:23:22,880
 by the most powerful religious leaders in the land.

461
00:23:22,880 --> 00:23:25,520
 But when they were filled by the Holy Spirit,

462
00:23:25,520 --> 00:23:27,720
 they shifted the focus.

463
00:23:27,720 --> 00:23:30,480
 Suddenly, it was the high priest and the rulers

464
00:23:30,480 --> 00:23:32,880
 who were being put on trial,

465
00:23:32,880 --> 00:23:36,800
 not before human caught, but before God himself.

466
00:23:36,800 --> 00:23:40,920
 Now the question was not about Peter and John's authority,

467
00:23:40,920 --> 00:23:43,920
 but about the leaders' willingness to obey God.

468
00:23:43,920 --> 00:23:49,040
 The wisdom of the Holy Spirit enabled Peter and John

469
00:23:49,040 --> 00:23:51,360
 to see through the intimidation,

470
00:23:51,360 --> 00:23:53,400
 to stand firm in their conviction,

471
00:23:53,400 --> 00:23:56,280
 and to expose a deeper truth.

472
00:23:56,280 --> 00:23:59,080
 Who are you really serving?

473
00:23:59,080 --> 00:24:01,680
 Whose voice are you listening to?

474
00:24:01,680 --> 00:24:06,680
 The same spirit-given wisdom is what we need

475
00:24:06,680 --> 00:24:09,520
 when we face accusation or pressure,

476
00:24:09,520 --> 00:24:13,080
 so that we too can discern what is truly right

477
00:24:13,080 --> 00:24:16,720
 in God's eyes, and to have the courage to stand before him.

478
00:24:16,720 --> 00:24:21,720
 Second, this is a mirror for us.

479
00:24:21,720 --> 00:24:25,480
 When we are under pressure or fear,

480
00:24:25,480 --> 00:24:28,960
 which could be real, and I'm not undermining

481
00:24:28,960 --> 00:24:31,160
 how challenging life could be.

482
00:24:31,160 --> 00:24:37,520
 When we are asked to compromise,

483
00:24:37,520 --> 00:24:40,680
 or struggling to hold on to our faith,

484
00:24:40,680 --> 00:24:43,800
 Peter and John's question is for us too.

485
00:24:43,800 --> 00:24:47,800
 Can I hear God's voice in this?

486
00:24:47,800 --> 00:24:51,880
 Or am I just listening to the loudest voices in the world?

487
00:24:51,880 --> 00:24:57,680
 Am I serving out of my own comfort, or serving Christ?

488
00:24:57,680 --> 00:25:01,040
 Their response wasn't stubbornness,

489
00:25:01,040 --> 00:25:03,480
 or trying to argue their way through,

490
00:25:03,480 --> 00:25:05,160
 but they're just being honest.

491
00:25:05,160 --> 00:25:09,800
 I cannot help but speak about what we have seen or heard.

492
00:25:09,800 --> 00:25:13,480
 And I feel like in our midst right now,

493
00:25:13,480 --> 00:25:18,240
 there are times when we cannot hold on anymore.

494
00:25:18,240 --> 00:25:21,600
 When we need to be strong, and we need to remember

495
00:25:21,600 --> 00:25:25,160
 the goodness of Jesus, but it's just so difficult.

496
00:25:25,160 --> 00:25:27,320
 And that's why we gather together in church,

497
00:25:27,320 --> 00:25:30,520
 because when you talk about God's goodness in your life,

498
00:25:30,520 --> 00:25:33,200
 this is going to happen to your friends sitting next to you.

499
00:25:33,200 --> 00:25:37,480
 When you testify the goodness and the grace in Jesus' name,

500
00:25:37,480 --> 00:25:40,600
 this is going to stir up a power in this community,

501
00:25:40,600 --> 00:25:43,880
 that not because we can't do it, but in community,

502
00:25:43,880 --> 00:25:48,800
 together we can witness the power and the grace of God.

503
00:25:48,800 --> 00:25:51,520
 So never stop coming back, never stop meeting,

504
00:25:51,520 --> 00:25:53,840
 and just don't come and be yourself,

505
00:25:53,840 --> 00:25:58,400
 but I encourage you to be in community, to make friends,

506
00:25:58,400 --> 00:26:01,600
 because today you can be someone else's encouragement,

507
00:26:01,600 --> 00:26:06,600
 you are going to testify the power and the holiness of God.

508
00:26:06,600 --> 00:26:11,640
 And tomorrow, others might do the same for you.

509
00:26:11,640 --> 00:26:14,120
 And we are building this church together

510
00:26:14,120 --> 00:26:16,360
 in this uncharted season.

511
00:26:16,360 --> 00:26:18,560
 This is uncharted season for us,

512
00:26:18,560 --> 00:26:20,400
 and we're gonna do this together,

513
00:26:20,400 --> 00:26:24,600
 because it is God who brought us all together in this place.

514
00:26:24,600 --> 00:26:25,440
 Amen?

515
00:26:29,320 --> 00:26:32,080
 Maybe God is inviting each of us

516
00:26:32,080 --> 00:26:35,160
 to respond like Peter and John.

517
00:26:35,160 --> 00:26:38,600
 When we face fear, confusion, or pressure,

518
00:26:38,600 --> 00:26:42,880
 Peter and John's words can be a filter for our hearts.

519
00:26:42,880 --> 00:26:45,720
 Who am I listening to right now?

520
00:26:45,720 --> 00:26:49,440
 Are my actions led by God's perspective,

521
00:26:49,440 --> 00:26:52,640
 or just shaped by the outside pressure?

522
00:26:52,640 --> 00:26:57,000
 So often, just honestly asking ourselves these questions

523
00:26:57,000 --> 00:27:00,880
 helps us see what's really happening inside.

524
00:27:00,880 --> 00:27:03,520
 Peter and John didn't claim to know everything,

525
00:27:03,520 --> 00:27:05,200
 or have all the answers.

526
00:27:05,200 --> 00:27:06,480
 They just honestly said,

527
00:27:06,480 --> 00:27:09,040
 "We've seen, heard, and experienced God,

528
00:27:09,040 --> 00:27:11,280
 "and we can't be quiet about it."

529
00:27:11,280 --> 00:27:15,440
 Maybe for you, having the courage to take the next step

530
00:27:15,440 --> 00:27:18,040
 isn't about figuring out all the answers,

531
00:27:18,040 --> 00:27:21,080
 or know where you're going,

532
00:27:21,080 --> 00:27:25,000
 but just be honest about your journey with God,

533
00:27:25,000 --> 00:27:28,480
 and letting that truth be the foundation

534
00:27:28,480 --> 00:27:30,120
 for your next step of faith.

535
00:27:30,120 --> 00:27:33,920
 When we're hesitant or struggling,

536
00:27:33,920 --> 00:27:35,960
 Jesus doesn't walk away.

537
00:27:35,960 --> 00:27:39,520
 He comes to meet us right at the place

538
00:27:39,520 --> 00:27:43,560
 where we're most afraid, most resistant,

539
00:27:43,560 --> 00:27:46,200
 and least willing to face.

540
00:27:46,200 --> 00:27:50,320
 Grace isn't just for the moments when we're doing well.

541
00:27:50,320 --> 00:27:54,200
 It's even more for the times we fail,

542
00:27:54,200 --> 00:27:56,960
 we fear, or we want to hide.

543
00:27:56,960 --> 00:28:01,000
 The same Jesus who sought Peter

544
00:28:01,000 --> 00:28:03,120
 after he denied him three times,

545
00:28:03,120 --> 00:28:05,800
 restored him and embraced him,

546
00:28:05,800 --> 00:28:08,680
 and he does the same for me and for you.

547
00:28:08,680 --> 00:28:14,360
 He comes to find us, welcomes us, forgives us,

548
00:28:14,360 --> 00:28:16,240
 and encourage us to move forward.

549
00:28:16,240 --> 00:28:21,520
 Even when you feel your faith or courage isn't enough,

550
00:28:21,520 --> 00:28:24,200
 his love is enough to cover you.

551
00:28:24,200 --> 00:28:30,280
 His love, his power, his wisdom

552
00:28:30,280 --> 00:28:32,440
 is bigger than our decision.

553
00:28:32,440 --> 00:28:37,600
 But the work we need to put in is to surrender.

554
00:28:37,600 --> 00:28:41,480
 The work that we need to put in is to walk with him,

555
00:28:41,480 --> 00:28:43,280
 be close to him.

556
00:28:43,280 --> 00:28:47,480
 The work that we need to put in is to check our intentions.

557
00:28:47,480 --> 00:28:48,800
 I often hear the saying,

558
00:28:48,880 --> 00:28:52,080
 God is not going to be mad at us and go,

559
00:28:52,080 --> 00:28:53,320
 you want to serve the orphans,

560
00:28:53,320 --> 00:28:55,240
 but I told you to serve the children.

561
00:28:55,240 --> 00:28:56,920
 He's not gonna do that.

562
00:28:56,920 --> 00:28:58,760
 But what we need to figure out is,

563
00:28:58,760 --> 00:29:02,480
 what is my intention of wanting to do that?

564
00:29:02,480 --> 00:29:06,280
 Am I doing it, the ministry, church thing,

565
00:29:06,280 --> 00:29:07,680
 school thing, work thing,

566
00:29:07,680 --> 00:29:10,680
 out of my own glory and my own benefit?

567
00:29:10,680 --> 00:29:15,040
 Or is my intention focusing on God?

568
00:29:15,640 --> 00:29:20,640
 Jesus is going to wrap us up

569
00:29:20,640 --> 00:29:22,840
 when we're feeling the weakest

570
00:29:22,840 --> 00:29:26,440
 and inviting us not to rely on our own strength,

571
00:29:26,440 --> 00:29:29,240
 but to trust his love and faithfulness

572
00:29:29,240 --> 00:29:33,600
 and bring our weakness closer to him.

573
00:29:33,600 --> 00:29:37,000
 And I'd like to invite the worship team to come up.

574
00:29:37,000 --> 00:29:41,520
 As we move into a time of prayer and ministry,

575
00:29:41,520 --> 00:29:43,920
 we need to be open to God's love.

576
00:29:43,920 --> 00:29:47,200
 And as we move into a time of prayer and ministry,

577
00:29:47,200 --> 00:29:51,000
 maybe there's something that God is bringing up

578
00:29:51,000 --> 00:29:51,960
 in your heart.

579
00:29:51,960 --> 00:29:57,880
 Maybe a place of uncertainty, a fear,

580
00:29:57,880 --> 00:30:00,840
 or step he's inviting you to take.

581
00:30:00,840 --> 00:30:04,680
 So I would like to invite you to close our eyes

582
00:30:04,680 --> 00:30:07,400
 and just be ministered.

583
00:30:07,400 --> 00:30:09,800
 (soft music)

584
00:30:09,800 --> 00:30:17,600
 A lot has been said today.

585
00:30:17,600 --> 00:30:24,240
 But then what is the most important word

586
00:30:24,240 --> 00:30:26,160
 that needs to be spoken?

587
00:30:26,160 --> 00:30:28,800
 It's the word that the Holy Spirit

588
00:30:28,800 --> 00:30:30,320
 is speaking to you right now.

589
00:30:35,800 --> 00:30:40,360
 Maybe there's something that you have inside your heart

590
00:30:40,360 --> 00:30:42,600
 that you know that you want to take,

591
00:30:42,600 --> 00:30:45,080
 but there's fear.

592
00:30:45,080 --> 00:30:49,880
 Maybe there are doubts.

593
00:30:49,880 --> 00:30:56,600
 Jesus is not telling you to brush it away.

594
00:30:56,600 --> 00:30:58,080
 Just have courage, brush it away.

595
00:30:58,080 --> 00:31:01,360
 No, he said, look at that.

596
00:31:01,360 --> 00:31:02,760
 Look at that fear.

597
00:31:02,760 --> 00:31:05,000
 Look at the thing that you're afraid of

598
00:31:05,000 --> 00:31:08,800
 and tell Jesus, why are you afraid of that?

599
00:31:08,800 --> 00:31:15,000
 What is triggering you?

600
00:31:15,000 --> 00:31:17,760
 What is bothering you?

601
00:31:17,760 --> 00:31:21,080
 And you can give it to Jesus.

602
00:31:21,080 --> 00:31:29,720
 Maybe he's showing you the next step that you should take.

603
00:31:30,720 --> 00:31:33,120
 (soft music)

604
00:31:33,120 --> 00:31:40,600
 And I just pray that in this time,

605
00:31:40,600 --> 00:31:43,960
 you're going to open your heart and open your eyes.

606
00:31:43,960 --> 00:31:55,320
 And just like a child, we can run to Jesus,

607
00:31:55,320 --> 00:31:56,920
 his accepting love.

608
00:31:58,200 --> 00:31:59,680
 It's going to embrace you.

609
00:31:59,680 --> 00:32:02,260
 (gentle music)

610
00:32:02,260 --> 00:32:12,260
 [BLANK_AUDIO]

